  "show": {
    "date": "1987-07-31",
    "comments": [
      "\"Hello there: top of the evening and all that. Welcome to the Friday Rock Show: not TV on the radio, but DB on the radio, Dante Bonutto, holding the fort and the mike while Tommy's off on his hols. Can you really build a life-size model of Lemmy out of sand and shells? Well, find out when Tommy gets back.\"",
      "Dante sounds as though he is reading from a script for the most part, although it is his first time at the helm of a radio show (he claims). He ends the show by playing three versions of Black Diamond, for no good reason, especially since he labels the first just OK and the second terrible.",
      "After the Michael White track, Bonutto says something like \"Michael White might not be able to teach Robert Plant anything about sucking lemons, but quite frankly I don't really care...\"."
    ]
  },
